Hi, all!

I'm working on a project where a secure TELNET connection is required.  I am aware of some work on standardization of an encryption option for TELNET.  Can somebody inform me on the status of this work?  RFC 1340 -- Assigned Numbers lists an encryption option for TELNET but RFC 1540 -- Internet Official Protocol Standards does not mention it at all.  I am aware of two different proposals for an encryption option for TELNET.  The first by David Borman dated April 1990 and the second by Lawrence Brown and Gilje Jaatun dated December 1991.  Has anything else been done?


-- Rolf


